Class SecuritySchema

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.model.security.transport.SecuritySchema

  • public final class SecuritySchema
extends Object
    A container for the SecurityDimensions and SecurityTagGroups that can be used for Items in the Intelligence Analysis Platform.

    • Constructor Detail

      • SecuritySchema

        public SecuritySchema(String id,
              long version,
              Collection<SecurityTagGroup> securityTagGroups,
              Collection<SecurityDimension> accessSecurityDimensions,
              Collection<SecurityDimension> grantSecurityDimensions)
        Constructs a new SecuritySchema, initializing all mandatory fields.

        Note: SecuritySchemas are not validated at creation. Rather, the Intelligence Analysis Platform validates them during execution of initializeSecuritySchema() in the administration service..

        Parameters:
        id - A String containing the identifier of this SecuritySchema.
        version - The version number of this SecuritySchema.
        securityTagGroups - The SecurityTagGroups that this SecuritySchema contains.
        accessSecurityDimensions - The "access" SecurityDimensions that this SecuritySchema contains.
        grantSecurityDimensions - The "grant" SecurityDimensions that this SecuritySchema contains.
